  "prompt": "I'm doing my first pyromancer build in Dark Souls 3. What stats do I need to build on to be most effective?",
  "response": "For a pyromancer build in Dark Souls 3, you'll want to focus on the following stats:\n\n1. Intelligence (INT) - Increases spell scaling and damage for pyromancies\n2. Faith (FTH) - Also increases spell scaling and damage for pyromancies\n3. Attunement (ATT) - Increases number of spell slots and FP (FP is like mana)\n4. Vigor (VIG) - Increases health points for survivability\n\nThe ideal approach is to level both INT and FTH equally, as pyromancies scale with the average of these two stats. Aim for around 40-45 in both. Attunement should be around 20-24 to get enough spell slots. Vigor depends on your playstyle, but 27-30 is a good starting point.\n\nYour starting class should ideally be Pyromancer for the best initial stat distribution. Don't neglect Endurance (END) for stamina, and put just enough points in Strength and Dexterity to use your preferred weapons.\n\nKey pyromancy tools like the Pyromancy Flame and rings that boost fire damage will also help your build.",
